Interface Symbol

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    TypeSymbol
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayConstantSymbol, BaseSymbol, ComponentSymbol, ConstantSymbol, ControllerSymbol, EventHandlerSymbol, FieldSymbol, FlowSymbol, ImportSymbol, InstanceSymbol, InterfaceSymbol, MethodDeclarationSymbol, ModelSymbol, PrimitiveTypeSymbol, ReferenceSymbol, SpaceSymbol, SymbolWithScope, VariableSymbol, ViewSymbol

    public interface Symbol
    A generic programming language symbol. A symbol has to have a name and a scope in which it lives. It also helps to know the order in which symbols are added to a scope because this often translates to register or parameter numbers.
